parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission shift cable can cause the vehicle to roll away or become stuck in gear, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The gear shift lever feels loose or does not move
the vehicle rolls away or moves unexpectedly
the transmission fails to engage into gear
the vehicle stalls or hesitates to start.

the vehicle's electrical systems malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various issues, including brake light malfunctions, power lock failures, and engine stalling, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag and traction control systems can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded, especially if the airbag deploys unexpectedly or the traction control system malfunctions.
